# Design Tokens and Visual Style Rule

Use reusable design tokens for the Monica auth redesign.

Do not scatter repeated colors, radii, shadows or transition values across files.

## Visual Direction

The interface must feel:

- dark;
- premium;
- elegant;
- glass-like;
- minimal;
- modern;
- spacious;
- polished;
- professional.

## Recommended Color Tokens

Use these as a starting point and tune visually against the references:

```css
:root {
  --auth-bg-main: #0B1020;
  --auth-bg-deep: #070A14;

  --auth-card-bg: rgba(14, 20, 39, 0.74);
  --auth-card-border: rgba(136, 158, 255, 0.22);

  --auth-text-primary: #F6F8FF;
  --auth-text-secondary: #AAB4D4;
  --auth-text-muted: #737D99;

  --auth-accent: #5B7CFF;
  --auth-accent-strong: #3F6BFF;
  --auth-accent-violet: #7A5CFF;

  --auth-input-bg: rgba(7, 11, 22, 0.76);
  --auth-input-border: rgba(158, 172, 216, 0.30);
  --auth-input-border-hover: rgba(178, 190, 232, 0.48);
  --auth-input-border-focus: rgba(91, 124, 255, 0.95);

  --auth-error: #FF5F7A;
  --auth-success: #45D69A;
  --auth-warning: #F5B84B;

  --auth-radius-card: 28px;
  --auth-radius-control: 13px;

  --auth-transition-fast: 140ms ease;
  --auth-transition-base: 180ms ease;
}
```

## Typography

Use a modern sans-serif font stack:

```css
font-family:
  Inter,
  Manrope,
  "SF Pro Display",
  "Segoe UI",
  system-ui,
  -apple-system,
  BlinkMacSystemFont,
  sans-serif;
```

Recommended hierarchy:

```css
.brand {
  font-size: 48px;
  line-height: 1;
  font-weight: 800;
  letter-spacing: -0.04em;
}

.page-title {
  font-size: 36px;
  line-height: 1.15;
  font-weight: 750;
  letter-spacing: -0.03em;
}

.helper-text {
  font-size: 17px;
  line-height: 1.6;
  font-weight: 400;
}

.label {
  font-size: 15px;
  line-height: 1.3;
  font-weight: 500;
}
```

Tune exact values to the references.

## Brand

The brand name must remain:

```txt
Monica
```

Use gradient text for the brand.

Example:

```css
.brand {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6EA2FF 0%, #4D73FF 45%, #8A5CFF 100%);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  background-clip: text;
  color: transparent;
}
```

If the reference includes a small sparkle/star near the brand, recreate it as SVG or CSS, not as part of a screenshot.

## Glass Card

The auth card should use:

- semi-transparent dark background;
- subtle border;
- soft shadow;
- inner highlight;
- backdrop blur;
- large rounded corners.

Example starting point:

```css
.auth-card {
  border-radius: 28px;
  background: rgba(14, 20, 39, 0.74);
  border: 1px solid rgba(136, 158, 255, 0.22);
  box-shadow:
    0 32px 90px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.48),
    inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  backdrop-filter: blur(22px);
}
```
